The paper deals with auction mechanisms, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The use of linear programming and totally unimodular matrices suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the fields of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and combinatorics (cs.CC). Finally, the study of truthful auction mechanisms involves optimization and decision-making, which are also relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
